(nL2TLBEntries, nDCacheTLBWays).explanation: These are independent cache configuration parameters that operate at different levels of the memory hierarchy and do not directly influence each other's settings;

(nL2TLBEntries, nL2TLBWays).explanation: Both are independent configuration parameters of the L2 TLB structure where entries and ways are orthogonal design choices that don't causally affect each other;

(nL2TLBEntries, DCacheMiss).explanation: Increasing L2 TLB entries reduces TLB misses which decreases the frequency of page table walks, thereby reducing data cache pollution and potentially lowering data cache miss rates;
